<subSubSection pageNumber="279" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="279">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="279">Note:</emphasis>
Wijnands (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="279">Taxon</emphasis>
22: 109-114. 1973) argued that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Druce" authorityYear="1913" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Sansevieria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="hyacinthoides" variety="guineensis">
var. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="279">guineensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, not 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Druce" authorityYear="1913" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Sansevieria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="hyacinthoides" variety="zeylanica">
var. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="279">zeylanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was the typical variety of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Aletris" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hyacinthoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="279">A. hyacinthoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, an argument accepted by the Committee for Spermatophyta (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="279">Taxon</emphasis>
23: 823. 1973). Consequently, 
<taxonomicName authority="(L.) Druce" authorityName="Druce" authorityYear="1913" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Sansevieria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hyacinthoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="279">Sansevieria hyacinthoides</emphasis>
(L.) Druce
</taxonomicName>
was accepted as the correct name for what Stearn called 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="279">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Aloë">Aloe</normalizedToken>
guineensis
</emphasis>
(L.) Jacq., listed as the type of 
<taxonomicName authority="Thunb. in App." authorityName="Thunb. in App." class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Sansevieria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="279">Sansevieria</emphasis>
Thunb. in App.
</taxonomicName>
III of the ICBN.
</paragraph>
